stimulus:
Welcome to the experiment!

[press any key to continue]

In this experiment you will make decisions about whether to draw a card to get a variable payout or take a sure-thing payout.

[press any key to continue]

Here is what your choice might look like. On the left is a deck of cards that has variable payouts and on the right a sure-thing offer of 100 points.

[press any key to continue]
+100

You will press the 'F' key to choose the left-side option (deck).
You will press the 'J' key to choose the right-side option (sure-thing offer).

[press any key to continue]
+100

If you choose the deck, you will get that card's hidden offer.

The offer could be a positive or negative.

[press any key to continue]
+100

In this case the hidden card was worth +200 points, so the variable deck was a better than the sure-thing.

[press any key to continue]
+200
+100

On this trial, the hidden card was worth -150 points, so the sure-thing was better than the variable deck.

[press any key to continue]
-150
+100

Every decision involves a different deck of cards with variable payouts.
Some decks are better on average and some decks are worse on average.

[press any key to continue]

To give you a sense of whether the deck is good or bad, you will be shown 5 cards from each deck before you are asked to choose between the variable deck option and the sure-thing option.

To see these example cards you will press the SPACE BAR.

[press any key to continue]

To help you keep track of how well you are doing, your score will be shown at the bottom of the screen.

You will start from 1000 points and can both gain and lose points.

Note that you will only gain or lose points when you choose between the two options.

[press any key to continue]

In the experiment you will make decisions about 180 different decks. This should take about 20-30 minutes to complete.

When you are ready to begin we will try a few example games to make sure that everything makes sense.

[press any key to continue]

The words ""New Deck"" will appear each time there is a new deck with a different average payoff. The task automatically moves on after 1 second.

For this practice game, press SPACE BAR to continue.
